description: Acer Super ZX and Super ZX Pro handsets have been unveiled in India. Both handsets pack 5,000mAh batteries each with support for 33W wired fast charging and run on stock Android 15 out-of-the-box. They are equipped with stereo speakers and support dual SIM and 5G connectivity. The Acer Super ZX is powered by a MediaTek Dimensity 6300 SoC, while the Super ZX Pro carries a MediaTek 7400 chipset.
title: Acer Super ZX With 64-Megapixel Rear Camera Launched in India Alongside Super ZX Pro

description: Bharti Airtel on Tuesday announced a strategic partnership with Blinkit for quick deliveries of SIM cards in select cities in India. It enables customers to get doorstep deliveries of both prepaid and postpaid Airtel SIM cards by paying a nominal convenience fee. The telecom operator will also offer the facility of porting SIM cards from another service provider to Airtel’s network.
title: Airtel Partners With Blinkit for 10-Minute Home Delivery of SIM Cards in Select Indian Cities

description: Apple is developing new techniques to analyse user data patterns and aggregated insights to improve its artificial intelligence (AI) features. The Cupertino-based tech giant shared these differential privacy techniques on Monday, highlighting that these methods will not breach users’ privacy. Instead, the company is focusing on gathering data such as usage trends and data embeddings to measure and improve its text generation tools and Genmoji.
title: Apple Is Improving Apple Intelligence Features Using Differential Privacy Techniques

description: Assassin’s Creed Shadows is a bona fide success for Ubisoft. The action-adventure title has been the best-selling game in the US throughout the three weeks since its launch, as per data from market research firm Circana.
title: Assassin's Creed Shadows Best Selling Game in the US Since Launch: Circana

description: Asus ExpertBook P Series laptops were launched in India on Tuesday comprising three models — ExpertBook P1, ExpertBook P3, and ExpertBook P5. Aimed at businesses and professionals, the laptops come with artificial intelligence (AI) capabilities courtesy of in-built AI engines, military-grade durability, and enterprise-grade service support. Asus says the ExpertBook P series is powered by up to Intel Core Ultra Series 2 processors along with security solutions such as a dedicated TPM 2.0 chip, self-healing BIOS, and Optical Chassis Intrusion Alert.
title: Asus ExpertBook P Refreshed With Up to Intel Core Ultra Series 2 CPUs in India

description: Crypto exchanges Binance, KuCoin, and MEXC acknowledged that some of their services suffered issues owing to an Amazon Web Services (AWS) on Tuesday, March 15. The users of these exchanges panicked on social media after they could not access the services on these exchanges.
title: Binance Among Crypto Exchanges Hit by Amazon Web Services Outage

description: The Department of Telecom (DoT) has instructed India's top three telecom operators to complete inter-operator trials for the Caller Name Presentation (CNAP) feature. A new report reveals that the CNAP technology, requiring additional network infrastructure for older 2G networks, will be exclusive to 4G and 5G smartphone users when it is rolled out.
title: DoT Reportedly Asks Telcos to Complete Caller ID System Trials, Submit Report by April 18

description: Ancient green oceans may return due to climate change.
title: Earth’s Oceans Were Once Green, And Scientists Say They Could Shift Color Again

description: Google Classroom is getting a new artificial intelligence (AI) feature that can generate questions on a particular topic based on information shared with the tool. Announced on Monday, the feature is currently available to the paid Education tier of Google Workspace users. Powered by Gemini, the tool can generate a wide variety of questions that can be used to assess students.
title: Google Classroom Updated With Gemini-Powered Questionnaire and Quiz Generation Features

description: Google Photos integration with the Gemini app on Android is reportedly now rolling out to users. Earlier this month, the Mountain View-based tech giant confirmed that the integration was being released to the public. With this, users can now ask Gemini questions about their photos to either locate specific images or derive information from within the images saved in Google Photos.
title: Google Photos Integration in Gemini’s Android App Reportedly Rolling Out to Users

description: Honor appears to be gearing up to unveil the Honor GT Pro as a premium gaming smartphone. The launch date of the phone is still under wraps, but an Honor executive has teased the design and specifications of the Honor GT Pro. The phone is confirmed to come with a 144Hz refresh rate display and a 3D ultrasonic fingerprint sensor.
title: Honor GT Pro Design, Specifications Revealed; Teased to Get 144Hz Screen, Ultrasonic Fingerprint Sensor

description: HP has opened pre-orders for its latest generation of OmniBook AI PCs in India, with prices starting at Rs. 78,999. The new OmniBook series includes four models — OmniBook Ultra 14, OmniBook X Flip 14, OmniBook 7 and OmniBook 5. All models are equipped with Intel Lunar Lake and AMD Strix Point and Krackan Point processors.
title: HP OmniBook AI PCs Refreshed With Intel Lunar Lake, AMD Krackan Point CPUs: Price, Specifications

description: Infinix has revealed the camera, chipset and battery details of the Note 50s 5G+ handset ahead of its April 18 India launch. Previous teasers claimed that the upcoming smartphone will be India's slimmest 144Hz curved AMOLED smartphone in its segment. It will be available in metallic finishes and vegan leather back panels. The latter is confirmed to support a scent tech feature.
title: Infinix Note 50s 5G+ Confirmed to Feature 64-Megapixel Rear Camera Ahead of Launch in India

description: LG Xboom Buds have been launched in select global markets. They have an IPX4-rated splash-resistant build and carry graphene-coated dynamic drivers. Together with the case, the earphones are claimed to offer a total battery life of up to 30 hours. They are tuned by American music artist Will.i.am and they support active noise cancellation (ANC) and Auracast.
title: LG Xboom Buds TWS Earphones With Graphene Drivers, Up to 30 Hours Total Battery Life Launched

description: NASA and international scientists closely tracked asteroid 2024 YR4, which initially showed a rare 3 percent collision probability with Earth. Although the threat has now diminished, the incident highlights the importance of asteroid surveillance, open data, and upcoming space missions like NEO Surveyor.
title: NASA Shares Planetary Defense Strategy to Protect Earth From Potential Asteroid Strikes

description: PhonePe UPI Circle feature was launched in India on Tuesday, enabling primary users to authorise secondary users for payments even if they do not have their own bank accounts. Developed by NPCI, UPI Circle aims to broaden UPI usage and allow supervised spending. Here's everything you need to know about how PhonePe UPI Circle works.
title: PhonePe UPI Circle Feature With Seamless Payment Authorisation Launched in India

description: A team of international astronomers has identified a new sub-Neptune exoplanet that has been orbiting the star called GI 410. This has been a magnificent discovery in the area of science. This newly detected sub-Neptune exoplanet weighs approximately 8.5 Earth masses. The discovery was commenced by the use of the Radial Method, the technique that has been behind the identification of over 600 exoplanets.
title: Scientists Discover New Sub-Neptune Exoplanet Using Radial Velocity Detection Technique

description: In an interview with Gadgets 360, Polygon and Avail co-founders Sandeep Nailwal and Anurag Arjun share their thoughts on whether India should establish a Bitcoin reserve like the US. Nimen Shah, a senior chartered accountant and international tax advisor from Mumbai, contributed to the discussion by emphasising India’s turbulent history with crypto, which keeps the likelihood of such a reserve at bay for the time being.
title: Should India Follow the US and Establish a Bitcoin Reserve? Polygon, Avail Co-Founders Talk to Gadgets 360

description: Urban HX30 wireless headphones were launched in India on Monday. The over-the-ear headphones are equipped with 44mm audio drivers and feature touch controls. The Urban HX30 headphones offer support for Hybrid active noise cancellation (ANC) up to 32dB, a dual-microphone system, and include a single button that lets users switch between ANC and Transparency mode quickly. The Urban HX30 headphones are advertised to provide a maximum of 14 hours of playback time on a single charge.
title: Urban HX30 Wireless Headphones With Hybrid ANC, Up to 14-Hour Battery Life Launched in India

description: Vodafone Idea (Vi) has silently rolled out a new prepaid recharge plan for users in India. It offers benefits such as unlimited voice calls, daily data, and a set number of SMS per day. The plan is said to be available in select telecom circles in the country and comes with a service validity of 28 days. Alongside, prepaid Vi customers also benefit from extra data at night in addition to Weekend Data Rollover benefit.
title: Vodafone Idea (Vi) Silently Rolls Out Rs. 340 Recharge Plan With 1GB Daily Data, 28-Day Validity

description: The world's first baby was born following conception using a fully automated, digitally controlled intracytoplasmic sperm injection (ICSI) system. The system automates each of the 23 steps of the standard ICSI procedure, either under artificial intelligence (AI) control or under the digital control of a remote operator.
title: World's First Baby Born Through Fully Automated, Remotely Operated IVF Procedure

description: Realme has unveiled the design of the GT 7 handset ahead of its scheduled April 23 launch in China. The company has also confirmed the colour options of the phone and some of its key specifications. As per official posters shared by the company, the Realme GT 7 will be powered by a MediaTek Dimensity 9400+ SoC and pack a 7,200mAh battery in an 8.25mm thick body.
title: Realme GT 7 Design, Colour Options Revealed Ahead of April 23 Launch

description: Realme Narzo 80 Pro 5G and Narzo 80x 5G are now available for purchase in India. The latest Narzo series smartpones were launched in the country last week with MediaTek Dimensity chipsets and 6,000mAh batteries. The Pro model supports 80W charging, while the Narzo 80x 5G offers 45W fast charging. They come in two colour options and ship with Realme UI 6.0 based on Android 15.
title: Realme Narzo 80 Pro 5G, Narzo 80x 5G Now Available for Purchase in India: Price, Launch Offers

description: Google is increasing the minimum hardware specs for Android phones shipping with Google Mobile Services. New devices must now be equipped with more RAM and storage to ship with the Google Play Store and Play Services. While these specifications are well below most existing entry-level offerings, the update also enforces support for emergency contact sharing with emergency services.
title: Google Raises Minimum RAM and Memory Specifications for Android Smartphones

description: OnePlus Nord CE series handsets usually launch in May, followed by a numbered Nord model in July. Given this launch schedule, we were a bit surprised that there has been no information about the Nord CE 5 in the rumour mill. However, just yesterday, we got our first bit of information regarding its massive battery capacity. Now, there's another leak that has suggested some more hardware details of the Nord CE 5.
title: OnePlus Nord CE 5 Specifications Leaked; Said to Offer MediaTek Dimensity 8350 Chipset

description: This week, Apple removed 14 crypto exchange apps from its App Store in South Korea for not being in compliance with the country’s licensing regime. KuCoin and MEXC are among the impacted apps. Unregistered crypto businesses lack government protection and can pose financial risks to the users – which is why South Korea believes in cutting access to these platforms via popular apps stores like Apple's App Store and Google Play Store.
title: Apple Follows Google in Blocking 14 Unregistered Crypto Exchange Apps in South Korea

description: National Payments Corporation of India (NPCI) aims to draw an additional 200 million to 300 million Indians to UPI to “break their cash memory”. The outfit is piloting vision recognition technology to encourage higher UPI usage in parking payments, he added.
title: NPCI Targets 300 Million New Users for UPI Payments Platform

description: Mark Zuckerberg testified in a US antitrust trial this week. The FTC is seeking to force Meta to restructure Instagram and WhatsApp, challenging its reliance on ad revenue and its dominance in the social networking space. Meta has argued that its purchases of Instagram in 2012 and WhatsApp in 2014 have benefited users.
title: Meta's Mark Zuckerberg Disputes US Antitrust Case in Trial Testimony

description: OnePlus 13T will be unveiled next week in China. The BBK subsidiary, via Weibo, has confirmed the launch of the new smartphone in its home country. OnePlus has also opened pre-reservations for the OnePlus 13T via its official online store in China. The listing and Weibo teasers confirm the colour options and design of the upcoming phone. It is shown in three shades with a dual rear camera unit.
title: OnePlus 13T Confirmed to Launch on April 24; Colour Options, Display Details Revealed

description: OpenAI released three new artificial intelligence (AI) models on Monday. Staying true to its unusual naming convention, the company called this the GPT-4.1 family of AI models. There are three variants — GPT-4.1, GPT-4.1 mini, and GPT-4.1 nano. The San Francisco-based AI firm said that these models outperform the GPT-4o and GPT-4o mini across several metrics.
title: OpenAI Releases GPT-4.1 Family of AI Models in API, Said to Outperform GPT-4o

description: Electronic Arts has confirmed its next Star Wars game following leaks. Star Wars Zero Company is a single-player turn-based tactics title being developed by Bit Reactor in collaboration with Respawn Entertainment and Lucasfilm Games.
title: EA Announces Star Wars Zero Company, a Turn-Based Strategy Title From Respawn and Bit Reactor

description: Redmi A5 was launched in India on Tuesday as the latest budget offering by the Xiaomi sub-brand. The new 4G handset runs on an octa-core Unisoc T7250 chipset and carries a 5,200mAh battery. The Redmi A5 features a 32-megapixel dual rear camera unit and has a 6.88-inch display with a 120Hz refresh rate. The Redmi A5 is already been available for purchase in select international markets.
title: Redmi A5 With 5,200mAh Battery, Dual Rear Cameras Launched in India: Price, Specifications

description: Motorola Edge 60 Stylus was launched in India on Tuesday. The smartphone comes with a Snapdragon 7s Gen 2 SoC, a 5,000mAh battery with 68W wired and 15W wireless charging support, and a 50-megapixel triple rear camera unit. The Edge 60 Stylus is claimed to be the segment's first smartphone with a built-in stylus.
title: Motorola Edge 60 Stylus With Triple Rear Cameras, Built-In Stylus Launched in India

description: OmniVision OV50X has been launched as the company's newest 1-inch CMOS sensor aimed at flagship smartphones. It is the successor to the OV50H sensor from 2023. The company claims that the OmniVision OV50X camera sensor enables "movie-grade" video recording, offering up to 8K HDR support for high-end smartphones.
title: OmniVision OV50X 1-Inch Camera Sensor With 8K HDR Video Recording Support Launched

description: Samsung has unveiled the Galaxy XCover 7 Pro alongside the Galaxy Tab Active 5 Pro in select global markets. Both devices carry the Snapdragon 7s Gen 3 chipset and offer MIL-STD-810H durability. They have IP68-rated dust and water-resistant builds and Corning Gorilla Glass Victus+ display protection as well. The Galaxy XCover 7 Pro and Tab Active 5 Pro run on Android 15 with One UI 7 skin on top and are equipped with AI-backed features.
title: Samsung Galaxy XCover 7 Pro, Galaxy Tab Active 5 Pro With Snapdragon 7s Gen 3 SoC Launched

description: Samsung is said to be rolling out its Good Lock app to all countries. According to a report, users in Romania can download the app on their Galaxy devices to gain access to its extensive suite of customisation and personalisation features. Although the app has been around for several years now, its availability was limited to around 40 countries.
title: Samsung Begins Global Rollout of Good Lock App for Galaxy Devices Starting With Romania: Report

description: Apple on Monday released the iOS 18.5 Developer Beta 2 update for the iPhone to developers and beta testers. It is an iterative update and does not contain any noticeable new features. Building upon the release of the iOS 18.5 Developer Beta 1 earlier this month, the latest beta update for iPhone brings fixes for bugs related to the Apple Vision Pro app, StoreKit, Writing Tools, and others.
title: iOS 18.5 Developer Beta 2 With Fixes for Apple Vision Pro App, Writing Tools Rolls Out
